rawQuestions.Statements: I feel a moral obligation to meet higher standards than I expect from others.
I feel frustrated when things or people don’t live up to the standards I hold.
I focus on doing things the right way and avoiding mistakes.
I automatically see how things can be improved. I easily notice errors and want to correct them.
I focus on upholding fairness and justice as a matter of principle.
I feel a strong emotional need to be valued by the people I care about.
I feel happiest when I’m helping others and making them feel loved.
I focus on other people’s needs and how I can be helpful.
I tune in to how people feel around me, then I shape-shift to align with them and create positive rapport.
I focus on building meaningful connections and being there for people who need me.
I feel restless and unsatisfied if I’m not actively working toward something significant.
I feel good about myself when people see me as competent and successful.
I focus on accomplishing tasks and enjoy being productive. It can be difficult for me to slow down.
I excel at “reading a room”—I automatically tune in to what people value, so I can tailor how I present myself to impress them.
I focus on setting goals and then doing whatever it takes to accomplish them. When I define the result I want, I easily map a path to get there.
I feel emotions more intensely than most people, and I find deep meaning in beauty, art, and self-expression.
I feel a strong desire to feel understood, although I often feel misunderstood.
I focus on my inner emotional world and authentic self-expression.
I often compare myself to others, and I can easily see what's missing in myself.
I focus on finding meaning and depth in my experiences.
I feel drained when others make too many emotional or social demands on me.
I feel most comfortable when I have enough knowledge and resources.
I focus on gaining knowledge and understanding how things work.
I prefer relationships with clear boundaries so I can maintain my personal space and autonomy.
I focus on maintaining my independence and conserving my energy and resources.
I feel more confident when I have clear guidelines or authority to rely on.
I feel most at ease when I can rely on others to be consistent and dependable.
I focus much of my attention on risks, dangers, or threats.
I worry about not anticipating potential hazards. I try to forecast all potential problems.
I focus on finding reliable support and trustworthy people.
I feel restless or bored when stuck in routines or limitations.
I feel most excited by new ideas, experiences, and possibilities.
I focus much of my attention on interesting activities, stimulating ideas, and future possibilities.
I value being free from limitations in life. I don’t want to feel constrained by others or by situations.
I focus on keeping my options open and maintaining freedom.
I feel strong and independent, and I rarely let others see when I’m feeling vulnerable.
I feel energetic and enjoy taking on big challenges; I don’t back down when confronted with a difficult situation.
I focus on being direct and standing up for what I believe in.
I value honesty and directness. I tell the truth and want others to do the same.
I focus on being self-reliant and prefer to be in control of my own decisions and resources.
I feel anxious or unsettled by conflict or tension.
I feel most comfortable when things are peaceful and harmonious.
I focus on getting along with people and find it easy to blend in with the agendas of others.
I often merge with the people around me, easily seeing their perspectives and going along with what they want.
I focus on keeping the peace and excel at mediating or avoiding conflicts.
